HuNan Data Model

 
Search by table name, column name, or datatype. By default, the search will be for table name. Add a period (or start with a period) to search by column name. Add a colon (or start with a colon) to search by datatype. Basic regular expressions are supported. Want to run this locally? Just save this file locally and open it with your browser; no internet required. Adding "#query" to the end of the URL will automatically perform that search when the page is loaded, so you can share links to specific searches.
ExampleSearch for...
foobartable names containing "foobar"
.foobarcolumn names containing "foobar"
:intcolumns with datatype containing "int"
:concept.concept_idcolumns that are a foreign key to concept.concept_id
foobar.bazcolumn names containing "baz" within tables with names containing "foobar"
^foo$table with exact name "foo"
.^bar$columns with exact name "bar"
:^int$columns with exact datatype "int"
^foo.*bar$tables with names starting with "foo" and ending with "bar"
foo.*bar.^baz:varcharcolumn names starting with "baz" and datatype containing "varchar" within tables containing "foo" followed by "bar"
hotkeys: "/" jumps to search box, "?" toggle help. Click on help to dismiss.
